FBIS4-8734 "dreeu074_i_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-074 Daily Report 17 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Events in Gorazde -- 15 April Events in Gorazde -- 15 April Discusses Situation With Christopher LD1704172894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1600 GMT 17 Apr 94 LD1704172894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Haris Silajdzic, the prime minister of Bosnia-Herzegovina, today spoke on the phone with U.S. State Secretary Warren Christopher. Silajdzic warned Christopher about the critical situation in Gorazde. The aggressor has been attacking the town center and civilians in Gorazde. News reaching the U.S. public is not true. Something needs to be done urgently in order to save the lives of the tens of thousands of people, Silajdzic said among other things. Talking to Christopher, he stressed that reports said there were many wounded, and civilians were completely unprotected. According to Silajdzic, it is not only the credibility of the United Nations and NATO that is at stake, but also the credibility of the world democratic order.
